
[1]profoundly

   PROFOUND'LY, adv. Deeply; with deep concern.

   Why sigh you so profoundly?

   1. With deep penetration into science or learning; with deep knowledge
   or insight; as profoundly wise; profoundly skilled in music or
   painting.
